race.comment: SUMMER NIGHT (1) turned in a handy position before finishing second last start over 1612m at Kilmore, beaten a length. In a suitable race and looks well-placed to snare that elusive second career win. POETIC WHISPER (5) was prominent from the outset and fought on for second last start over 1300m at Mortlake, making it two minor placings in a row. Likely improver with strong prospects. CABLE DE VEGA (6) hit the frame two starts ago at Wodonga but ran below par last time when sixth and beaten 3.5 lengths over 1600m at Bairnsdale. This looks a sterner test than last time but on her best form she is capable of testing her rivals. TUNDRA (3) has not won for a long while. Last raced on November 7 when beaten 1.75 lengths into fourth at Hamilton over 1400m after being in the firing line on the bend. WARLIST (10) hasn't won since this meeting last year but should be primed after two runs back from a spell and looks ideally drawn.
